          <text><![CDATA[<p>Urges the President to: (1) revise the existing rules of engagement in Afghanistan and provide commanders the ability to target the Taliban outside of instances where they pose a direct threat to the United States or its allies; and (2) empower the commander of Operation Resolute Support with the authority to train, advise, and assist the Afghan National Defense Security Forces at the tactical level as missions require.</p> <p>Condemns terrorist activity in the Afghanistan region, especially the actions that Taliban forces have assisted and participated in against Afghan, U.S., and NATO forces.</p> <p>Expresses concern regarding the flow of foreign fighters to and from Afghanistan.</p> <ul> </ul> <ul> </ul>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
